JOHANNESBURG – Eskom has postponed its interim results announcement until early next year.
	
	The power utility says time is needed to review the impact of the 5,23 percent electricity tariff increase, approved by the National Energy Regulator of South Africa (Nersa). WATCH: Another electricity hike on the cards This was against Eskom’s request for an increase of 19,9 percent. READ: Lynne Brown introduces new Eskom board at special meeting Nersa approved a revenue application for R190 billion for the 2018/2019 financial year. The financial results were intended to be released before the end of December. eNCA